The Middelburg Police are currently conducting an investigation at Ultra Liquors on SADC Street. At about 08:00 this morning, a security guard was shot during a business robbery at the bottle store. Also read: Victim shot in armed business robbery  Business owners in the area told the Middelburg Observer journalist that they heard three gunshots coming from the liquor store. The security guard was wounded in his neck. It is believed that the suspects fled in the direction of Correctional Services on John Magagula Street. Also read: Street barricaded after armed robbery at Ultra Liquors 